## 1️⃣ What is a Function?
        A function is a block of code with a name that you can use again and again. 
Instead of writing the same code multiple times, you write it once inside a function and just call it whenever needed.

Real life example:
A washing machine is a function. You just press start (call it). You don't rewrite how it works every time!
  
 Why Use Functions?
- ✅ Write once, use many times
- ✅ Makes code clean and organized
- ✅ Easy to find and fix bugs
- ✅ Smart contracts are 100% built with functions

