## 🔑 Key Points to Remember

- `def` keyword creates a function
- Always handle edge cases (divide by zero, negative numbers)
- `return` is better than `print` inside functions — value can be reused
- Parameters go inside `()` when defining
- Arguments go inside `()` when calling
- Default parameters are used when no value is passed

